Topic 2: Arrow Functions
What is it?

A shorter way to write functions.

Old:

function greet() {
  return "Hello";
}

Modern:

const greet = () => {
  return "Hello";
};
Why Needed?

React uses functions everywhere.

Components are functions.

Event handlers are functions.

Hooks use functions.

Real-World Analogy

Traditional function:

Writing full postal address

Arrow function:

Using Google Maps shortcut

Same destination.

Less typing.

Syntax
const functionName = () => {};
Line-by-Line Explanation
const greet = () => {
  return "Hello";
};
const

